Mauritius Eyes Technology as Economic Pillar, l’Express Reports

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-04-22T08:15:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-22/mauritius-eyes-technology-as-economic-pillar-l-express-reports.html
Information and communication
technology is poised to become the first pillar of the Mauritian
economy by 2015, l’Express reported, citing ICT Minister
Tassarajen Pillay Chedumbrum.  Technology’s share in the country’s gross domestic product
was 5.7 percent in 2009 and the target is for it to exceed 7
percent in 2011, the minister said in an interview, according to
the Port Louis-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in  Port Louis  via Johannesburg at 
1933 or  gbell16@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 